Hmm.  Well, As you may or may not know -- Deathrun_Amazon_b3 was released.. three years ago.  

I had done a lot of editing to it since then, but I never really did get around to releasing it.  I just found out that the map itself is rather popular on Garry's mod deathrun servers (sassilization, represent!) so I decided to finally add the finishing touches and release it.

The map is still rather "Amateurish" as the bulk of it was made.. well.. three years ago, but the heart is still there.  

Some of the major changes include

- Fixing the speed of the water rising.

- Editing some traps to go along with the theme.

- Optimization.

- Texture fixes

There were a few more, but i mean.. I did most of them ages ago, so I can't exactly remember.   


I really don't plan on releasing this again, unless there is some cataclysmic problem.

This map was originally made for Garry's Mod deathrun for a mapping contest. It ended up getting first place. I decided to make a version for css. It is very well balanced for lots or little people.

It should be able to handle more than 64 players.

There was originally a working secret in the Garry's Mod version, but it doesn't work in CSS and I didn't feel like fixing it.

So, I made a deathrun map. This is of course in dev textures. For those of you who think they are overdone/boring, give it a try :) I try to work with the dev textures in a unique way. Having said that, here is the meat:

Traps:

16 total Button-sprung traps.
3 Side mini-traps.
Several of which are new and unique traps. I'm releasing this map as a beta for this reason. I'm sure there will be an issue with something that only mass testing can show. Ill wait a week for feedback either through steam or email. And release the final version next Monday.

There is 4 special grenades through out the map, there are not close together, as to shun people who just run for grenades and ignore the point of the map. 


There is a 60sec AFK timer in jail, so don't wait around. You will be killed, not teleported.

All buttons can only be pushed once, so make them count (you all can blame this on asshats who button spam)




Thanks to:

sct
Ryan S.
fail.boat
buck and faj (for those hard to answer questions)
everyone at intoxGaming.com, play on their deathrun server @ 72.5.86.29:27015
spoz
and whoever made deathrun_horrorhouse, I wouldnt have made this had I never played your map.

So yeah, thats it.


Beta 2 fixes:

Added a push on the long hall for the Ts
Fixed the team_activator_filter so the door for the Ts at the end doesnt open once one CT falls in the tank. (thx FAJ)

Beta 3 fixes:

Due to a MASSIVE amount of people getting confused in the map (..........) I've changed it to a more traditional deathrun style. if you fall off the platforms, or you get hit by a trap, you die. There is no 2nd chance.

Also changed the airaccel rate
added in the cubemaps i forgot.

Beta 4 fixes:

Increased the size of the smaller pillars on trap 1, also made the larger pillar re-rise after 10secs.
Trap 2 side doors lower after 60, if the Terrorist doesn't press the trap's button.
Trap 3 time was even to match the water rising with the trigger hurt.
Trap 4 was changed to make it where you walk across, as the hanging ladder was rather buggy.
Fixed the clipping issue on the exit door at the end of the map.
Also fixed the timing issue with the Fan on trap 4.
Most of the other traps were reduced by a few secs.
Trap 11 stops after 10secs now.
Aligned a few textures here and there.

Beta 5 fixes:

Added 2 more grenades (1 for me only though :P)
Trap 4 has a new fan, (made by Fibbs, support people who make pre-fabs!)
Also raised the walking beam on trap 4 by 9 units
Trap 5 was overhauled. Pillars are now 30x30 instead of 23x23. Also, only one pillars on each set can be lowered, once that one is lowered it stays and the other one is locked out.
Trap 8 is constantly on now, no button controls it.
Added an ambient sound, may be a little loud, so I may be turning it down in the future.
The gun room at the end now has a push so people cannot come back in it once they leave.
Added invisible walls so terrorist cannot fall off the platform at trap 5
Fixed a few more misaligned textures.

Final Version:
Changed the grenades at spawn a little, might mess with the players vision, but it should be ok.
Changed trap 1, doubled the amount of pillars, this was causing an issue where people could not see cause so many were on 1 pillar.
Reduced trap 3's time again.
Trap 5 looks snazzier
First side trap was tweaked so you wont be killed by the edges of the kill triggers.


Hopefully this will be the last revision, if there is another one, it wont be for a while.

Traps have been fixed, pictures to see what i have done.



TRAPS
1. Steam Trap: Added a invisible block above the vent that breaks on button, so that the "trigger_push" pushes you up no matter what, I also added larger walls all around so no wall glitching :).



2. Explosion: The trap where there is an explosion in the  air actually does a good amount of damage



3. Slow Steam: The steam now slows you only a bit, now you actually can press the button without people getting angry... It only now slows you slightly basically so t's don't have to react fast.



4. Fire: The fire trap had a glitch where you can walk far on the side and no get hurt ( PICTURE INCLUDED - IN HAMMER EDITOR ) I have now added a "trigger_hurt" so i don't have to change the flame, i also made the "trigger_hurt" built up damage so it acts like fire.


5. I have fixed NOOB event where the T doesn't get sent to the area, i have added a teleport and it now works fine 



I haven't changed this map in any other way other than just fixing it up fully.

A small map for a few players

You are member of the survival “DeathRun” game, and you with other players send out in the specially building “Radical City”. where prepared you some deaths traps, which you should be pass for win (CT), or conversely, activate traps for an other team (T)

Trap’s number – 14
All ending’s in the map – 4
Specially grenades – 4
CT SPAWN – 33
T SPAWN – 2

Deathrun A01 Radicalcity Walkthrough:
[http://youtu.be/QQDuhG_SM0U](http://youtu.be/QQDuhG_SM0U "")

Enjoy the game.

Instruction for installing a map:

Cstrike folder from the archive put in the root of the game Counter Strike Source, which is located on the directory steam/steamapps/common/counter strike source. Agree, if you are asked to replace the files.

_"On some operating systems to replace the entire access entirely to the new, and not just individual files that were in the new directory. It's rare, but if you have such a replacement directory, manually add the folder cstrike all files by category maps, materials and sound."_

Tips for normally map’s working:

* For other players don’t get error “Missing BSP” increase the number of team net_maxfilesize. Required size does not least 22.
* It is advisable to put on your server plugin NoBlock, which does not allow players to block each other's collision. Competing players can disrupt not only the gameplay on the map, as well as the players can get stuck if they were unsuccessful teleported into each other.
